  "doc_id": "27755",
  "text": "Once again, it should be noted that the global pilot could be generated by any parametric technique including linear methods; either by relying on regression splines with few knots or by using more complex approaches such as nonparametric regressions (for multiplicative bias correction in nonparametric regression, see [CITATION_1] ); or even by economic theory. However, even a simple and rough parametric guide is quite often enough to improve the estimate.",
